en: [Entries from the Cherokee Supreme Court Docket, 1823-1834, New Echota] 1826 Oct. 30

This is an excerpt from the Cherokee Supreme Court docket for the years 1823 to 1834. The Cherokee Supreme Court convened annually in New Echota beginning on the second Monday in October and lasting three weeks. This excerpt is from the Monday October 30, 1826 session of court, during which a civil case over the rights of a horse was heard. Entries from this Supreme Court docket cover items ch100-ch163.

body.value: Monday 30. The Court met according to adjournment Present John Martin , James Brown , Walter S. Adair & Jas. James Daniel Judges - Ruth Willson vs Bark Foreman Try right of a gray horse. The Court find for the ptff plaintiff Thirty dollars & cost of suit. Execution issued 3rd Nov. November
